<HR><H2>clear parameters</H2>
<H3>daemon@ATHENA.MIT.EDU (Tue Nov 16 04:01:35 1993
)</H3>
<PRE>
From: deforest@netcom.com (Robert de Forest)
To: coldstuff@MIT.EDU
Date: Tue, 16 Nov 93 0:54:50 PST

As a former MOO programmer, I have become used to clear props for default
options and the like. Parameters in ColdMUD do not appear to be clearable.
Is there a design reason for this or could it be changed?

I realize values can be initialized in .init(), but I'd like to be able to
change default values without looking for all the players who haven't changed
theirs.

I also wonder if unset parameters take up db space.

Robert de Forest / Crag@MostMOOs, tCD and MH.
-- 
</PRE>
